Day 5 — Tech Stack, Git Structure & Environment Configuration

*Pre-Build Initialisation | Spec Week Complete*

Jamisan Global Nigeria Ltd.

Version 1.0  |  Spec Week 2025  |  CONFIDENTIAL

# **5.1 Core Tech Stack**

Selected to prioritise backend database reliability and a high-speed, zero-reload frontend without the overhead of React or Vue.

| **Item** | **Detail** |
| --- | --- |
| **Database** | PostgreSQL — relational integrity mandatory for financial routing and agent ledger triggers. |
| **Backend** | Node.js with Express.js — high-concurrency webhook ingestion and API routing. |
| **Frontend UI** | HTML + Tailwind CSS + HTMX — seamless slide-out panels and tab switching without full page reloads. No build step needed for HTMX. |
| **Frontend reactivity** | Alpine.js — lightweight client-side state for On Break toggle, Order Bump field expansion, and modal interactions. |
| **Template engine** | EJS or plain HTML partials — HTMX swaps fragments, no full-page renders. |
| **Authentication** | JWT-based with role permissions. 2FA via TOTP for Directors, Ops Manager, and Accountant. |
| **Process manager** | PM2 — keeps Node.js running continuously and auto-restarts on server reboot. |
| **Reverse proxy** | Nginx — receives Cloudflare traffic on ports 80/443, handles SSL termination, routes to Node on port 3000. |
| **CDN and security** | Cloudflare — sits in front of VPS. Handles caching, DDoS protection, and bot filtering. All traffic enters via Cloudflare. |
| **Version control** | Git — private GitHub repository, one branch per module. |
| **Build tool** | Claude Code CLI — every session anchored to SPEC.md. |

# **5.2 Folder and File Structure**

Strict modular MVC layout. Supports 9 distinct role interfaces and 9 build modules without cross-contamination.

*⚠ This structure is the contract. Claude Code must not deviate from it. New files go in the correct directory — no flat dumping into root or src/.*

Monorepo layout — the ERP lives inside the existing jamisan GitHub repository:

jamisan/                          ← root repo (existing)

├── erp/                          ← Jamisan ERP (this project)

│   ├── SPEC.md

│   ├── .env.example

│   ├── package.json

│   └── src/

├── wordpress-plugins/            ← WP plugins and site work

├── landing-pages/                ← Sales page assets

└── README.md                     ← Root project index

Branch naming uses erp/ prefix to distinguish from other projects in the monorepo:

erp/feature/database-schema  |  erp/feature/auth-system  |  erp/feature/csr-interface  etc.

Full ERP folder structure inside jamisan/erp/:

